        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 1:27PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 126 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Philpott Dam, or near Bassett, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bassett...
Sanville...
Stanleytown...
Fairy Stone State Park...
Collinsville...
Oak Level...
and Philpott Dam.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
